===Etymology===
From the Russian verb [[ведать]] (to know). Cognate with English [[wit]] (to wit).

===Interjection===
'''ведь''' (ved’)

# [[after all]]
# [[indeed]], [[surely]]
# [[why]], [[well]]
# [[then]], you know, you see
# isn’t it?
#:*{{RUchar|Ведь [[уже|уже́]] [[поздно|по́здно]]}} — ''It’s late, isn’t it?''
#:*{{RUchar|Ведь [[он]] [[знаток|знато́к]]}} — ''After all, he’s an expert.''
#:*{{RUchar|Ведь [[я]] [[вы|вам]] [[говорить|говори́л]]!}} — ''But I told you!''